# Case 02 — Fileless Malware via Process Injection: Memory Forensics Investigation

**Case ID:** DFIR-2024-002  
**Classification:** High  
**Investigator:** Himanshu Chourasia  
**Tools:** Volatility 3, KAPE, Magnet AXIOM, CrowdStrike Falcon  
**Duration:** 9 hours (triage → memory acquisition → analysis → containment)

---

## Executive Summary

A financial services firm's EDR triggered a medium-severity alert on a workstation (`WS-FIN-047`) belonging to a Finance Analyst. Initial triage revealed no malicious files on disk — the threat was entirely fileless. Memory forensics using Volatility 3 uncovered a Cobalt Strike reflective DLL injected into a legitimate `spoolsv.exe` process. The attacker had used a malicious Excel macro delivered via a spear-phishing email to bootstrap the implant directly into memory, bypassing traditional AV and leaving minimal on-disk artefacts. Full attacker dwell time was estimated at 11 days.

