## Investigation Walkthrough

### Phase 1 — Live Memory Acquisition (KAPE)

Memory was acquired from the live system before any intervention using KAPE's memory acquisition module to preserve volatile artefacts.

```bash
# Acquire RAM via WinPmem (included in KAPE)
kape.exe --tsource C: --tdest D:\Cases\DFIR-2024-002\WS-FIN-047 \
  --target !SANS_Triage,EventLogs,Prefetch,ScheduledTasks \
  --module WinPmem

# Resulting memory image
WS-FIN-047.mem  (16 GB)
SHA-256: d4e8f2...a91c33  [VERIFIED]
```

