#### Malfind — Injected Code Detection

```bash
python vol.py -f WS-FIN-047.mem windows.malfind --pid 1492
```

```
Process: spoolsv.exe  PID: 1492
Start VPN: 0x1d0000   End VPN: 0x1d3fff
Protection: PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE   [SUSPICIOUS — RWX memory]
Vad Tag: VadS  (private memory — not backed by a file on disk)

Disassembly:
0x1d0000  4d 5a 90 00  MZ....   ← PE header in process memory
0x1d0004  03 00 00 00
0x1d0008  04 00 00 00
...
```

> **RWX (Read-Write-Execute) memory not backed by a file on disk** is a primary indicator of reflective DLL injection. A legitimate `spoolsv.exe` will never have executable private memory regions containing a PE header.

