#### Beacon Configuration Extraction

The injected DLL was dumped from memory and analysed:

```bash
python vol.py -f WS-FIN-047.mem windows.dumpfiles --pid 1492 --virtaddr 0x1d0000
```

Extracted PE submitted to **1768.py (Cobalt Strike config parser)**:

```
BeaconType:          HTTPS
C2 Server:           94.102.49.190,/jquery-3.3.1.min.js
Port:                443
Jitter:              15%
Sleep:               60000ms
UserAgent:           Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36
Watermark:           0x5109BF6D   ← Cobalt Strike Team Server license ID
Spawn_to x64:        %windir%\sysnative\dllhost.exe
```

> The **watermark** (0x5109BF6D) was cross-referenced with public threat intel — associated with a cracked Cobalt Strike build used by multiple financially-motivated threat actors.

